{{Refimprove|date=May 2007}}
Food served '''in a basket''', a '''basket platter''' or a '''basket with fries''' is a [[sandwich]] or other main-dish that is served on top of a [[basket]] of an accompanying foodstuff, usually [[french fries]].  The "basket" is usually either made of plastic and lined with paper, or is simply a disposable [[paperboard]] box or tray.  Sometimes the basket contains other [[side dish]]es as well, such as a container of [[coleslaw]] or a [[Pickled cucumber|pickle]]. This term is common in the [[Cuisine of the Midwest|Midwestern U.S.]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2012}}

==United Kingdom==
In the [[United Kingdom]] chicken in a basket, fried chicken on a bed of [[French Fries|chips]], was a popular dish in pubs and modest restaurants from the late 1960s through the 1970s.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Castelow|first1=Ellen|title=Food in Britain in the 1950s and 1960s|url=http://www.historic-uk.com/CultureUK/Food-in-Britain-in-the-1950s-1960s/|website=Historic UK|publisher=Historic UK Ltd|accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chicken In A Basket is back on the menu|url=http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/Chicken-Basket-menu/story-12793848-detail/story.html|website=Bristol Post|publisher=Local World Limited|accessdate=9 May 2015}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> 

In the 1970s the dish became so ubiquitous in UK venues offering evening entertainment that the locations became known to musicians and entertainers as the "chicken-in-a-basket circuit".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brewster|first1=Bill|title=Working Man’s Soul|url=http://www.djhistory.com/features/working-man-s-soul|website=DJhistory|publisher=DJ History Ltd|accessdate=9 May 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304062927/http://www.djhistory.com/features/working-man-s-soul|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kinsley|first1=Billy|title=The Merseys|url=http://www.triumphpc.com/mersey-beat/a-z/merseys3.shtml|website=Triumph PC Group|publisher=Triumph PC Group|accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Golden Garter night club|url=http://www.wythenshawe.btck.co.uk/GoldenGarterNightclub|website=Wythenshawe's History and Heritage|accessdate=9 May 2015}}</ref>

